Part 3: Model fit interpretation

According to our graphs, model 6, Pella-Tomlinson with inflated catches fit the model best. This was followed by Model 5: Pella-Tomlinson 0.5-0.9K with N0=K, which diverged slightly through time from its coded model. It would be interesting to analyze these predicted models with their coded models using a sensitivity analysis to better understand how they differ (the predicted models from the coded models).
